<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="472" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="77.[160,1372,288,916]" pageId="77" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[163,523,687,716]" pageId="77" pageNumber="472">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Grauer’s Large-headed Shrew is only known from the holotype collected in 1908 in the Itombwe Mountains. The region has been widely used for mining, farming, logging, and livestock grazing, and Grauer’s Large-headed Shrew is probably at risk of extinction. Additional sampling is needed to determine if it is still extant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
